        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-12-01T23:55:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-12-31T23:56:00-05:00" n="210" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d210">
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-chapter-head">[Würtemberg]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-volume-rules" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1873-12-01T23:59:59-04:56" notBefore="1873-01-01T00:00:00-04:56">undated</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">naturalization</hi>.</p>
                <p>An alien must belong to a commune in order to have the rights
                                        of citizenship, unless he has been named to some public
                                            employment.<note n="4" xml:id="d210fn4">Fœlix, vol. 1,
                                            p. 99.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">expatriation</hi>.</p>
                <p>The rights of citizenship are lost by emigration under the
                                        authority of government and by accepting foreign
                                        service.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
